Defendant Robert Lee Wade in court with attorney Alexis B Stewart.  Defendant Robert Lee Wade in custody.  
Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 6 YEARS, with credit for 137 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 3 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
- No controlled substances or alcohol;
- AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
- Urine screens;
- Seek and maintain employment;
- Participate in job and vocational training;
- Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
- Participate in Parenting counseling;
- Anger Management counseling/program;
- No contact with victims Novia L., Latoya R., and Chase Bank located at 210 W. Capital Drive, Glendale;
- Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
- Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 

The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given.  The Court orders the defendant REMANDED.
